name: Souza Lobo - Since 1932

reviews.review_text:
The Best shack in Calangute Beach by far!

Cool English  music and polite staff and a great view.

Unlike other places where only Hindi nonsense is played.

Food was delicious especially  the Golden fried calamari !
10/10

Without being discouraged, we made our way to Calangute Beach for lunch. Our choice was Souza Lobo, a restaurant steeped in history since 1932. The appeal of this establishment not only in its delectable cuisine but also in its picturesque seaside setting. While savouring our meal, we were captivated by the breathtaking sight of the azure sky blending with the ocean. As regular patrons of Souza Lobo since 2016, we can attest to its consistently excellent food and ambience. Despite the relatively high prices, it is a worthwhile indulgence, particularly for an early lunch or brunch during your time in North Goa.

Souza Lobo is located on Calangute Beach and it is best to walk from the main road or hotel to this place.

There are many seating options available, within the main restaurant building or outdoors towards the beach. There are many various size tables to suit singles, couples and large groups.

As with many restaurants in Goa, there are 2 menus - a food menu and a drinks menu. Both of which have a large selection of offerings. The staff will also show you some local catch of the day seafood.

Both drink and food options are of good quality and the restaurant is on the mid level pricing. The Goan fish curry with kingfish is of good flavour. I did ask for the full local spice level. Complementing this curry was fluffy rice and a butter chapatti that was soft and wonderful. The cucumber raita is refreshing and cleanses the palate when combined with the Goan fish curry.

The babimca dessert tasted amazing though the presentation was a little lacking and didn't match the presentation that was on the menu. It was a little sloppy in presentation.

Drinks were good with the papaya shake being of medium consistently and with a good amount of papaya flavour.
Cocktails were good also.

On this occasion the service was generally good though a little slow.

description:
### Discovering Souza Lobo: A Culinary Gem in Calangute, Goa

With a commendable rating of **4.2** from an impressive **10,267** reviews, **Souza Lobo** emerges as a beloved dining destination in Calangute, Goa. Since its establishment in **1932**, this iconic shack has become synonymous with authentic **Goan food** and is widely praised for specialties such as **King Fish** and **Xacuti**. The restaurant’s charming seaside location combined with its extensive menu and vibrant ambiance make it a must-visit spot for both locals and tourists alike.

### Ambiance & Design

As you approach Souza Lobo, you are welcomed by a vibrant atmosphere resonating with the sounds of cool English music, a refreshing change from the more ubiquitous Hindi tunes often played in the region. Photos shared by patrons highlight a blend of beach shack vibes and traditional décor, with comfortable seating options both indoors and outdoors, allowing diners to feast while gazing at the beautiful azure waters of Calangute Beach. The inviting setup creates an ideal setting for both leisurely meals and lively gatherings, catering to single diners, couples, and groups of friends.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The menu at Souza Lobo is a treasure trove for seafood lovers. Signature dishes such as the **Golden Fried Calamari** and the **Goan Fish Curry with Kingfish** consistently steal the spotlight. Guests have commented on the full-bodied flavors of the curry, expertly complemented by fluffy rice and a soft butter chapatti, while the refreshing **cucumber raita** serves as the perfect palate cleanser. Though some desserts, like the **Babimca**, may lack visual finesse in presentation compared to what is depicted on the menu, they still deliver in taste, leaving diners satisfied after their savory adventures. With both food and drink selections of good quality, the **papaya shake** and expertly crafted cocktails round out a delightful dining experience.

### Customer Experience & Service

Souza Lobo is lauded not only for its cuisine but also for its attentive and polite staff. Guest reviews frequently mention the friendly demeanor of the servers, contributing to a warm and welcoming experience, although some diners noted that service can be a tad slow during peak hours. The establishment offers two menus—one featuring food and the other for drinks—ensuring a wide array of choices. Guests have mentioned that reservations may be a wise choice, given the restaurant's popularity, particularly for lunch or brunch during the busy tourist season.

### Popularity & Reviews

The buzz surrounding Souza Lobo is palpable, with many regulars praising its consistency in delivering quality since their first visit. Patrons often recommend it as one of the best shacks in the area, underscoring the restaurant’s appeal not only to tourists but also to returning locals. Social media and review platforms overflow with glowing accounts, reinforcing its status as a culinary staple in North Goa.

### Visual Content Insights

The restaurant's visual appeal comes through in the vibrant customer-provided photos, showcasing the inviting atmosphere and delicious offerings. From striking images of the beautiful beachside setting to mouth-watering depictions of meticulously plated dishes, these visuals perfectly encapsulate the Souza Lobo experience. Each snapshot tells a story of underwater delights and scenic meals, drawing you in with the promise of a memorable dining encounter.

In conclusion, Souza Lobo stands out as more than just a restaurant; it is a cultural landmark that captures the essence of Goa’s illustrious culinary heritage. With its delicious offerings, stunning views, and inviting atmosphere, it is truly a gem on Calangute Beach—a place where food and relaxation come together seamlessly. Whether you're a long-time patron or a first-time visitor, Souza Lobo guarantees a delightful escape into the flavors of Goa.
